# Development Workflow

## First Time Setup
```bash
./hooks-install.sh                 # Install pre-commit hook
./scripts/dev-runner.sh --restart  # Build and start all services
```

## Dev Runner (Recommended)
```bash
./scripts/dev-runner.sh --restart      # Full rebuild + start
./scripts/dev-runner.sh --start        # Start without rebuild
./scripts/dev-runner.sh --stop         # Stop all
./scripts/dev-runner.sh --verify       # Check status
./scripts/dev-runner.sh --be-only-restart  # Backend process + Docker frontend
```

## SDK Development
**Python:** `cd sdks/python && pip install -e . && pytest`
**TypeScript:** `cd sdks/typescript && npm install && npm test`

Configure for local: `export OPIK_URL_OVERRIDE='http://localhost:8080'`

## Docker (E2E testing)
```bash
./opik.sh --build --port-mapping   # Full stack
./opik.sh --infra --port-mapping   # Infrastructure only
./opik.sh --clean                  # Reset (DATA LOSS)
```

## Troubleshooting
- Logs: `tail -f /tmp/opik-backend.log` or `/tmp/opik-frontend.log`
- Port conflicts: `lsof -i :8080` or `:5174`
- Reset: `./scripts/dev-runner.sh --stop && ./scripts/dev-runner.sh --restart`
- Hard reset: `./opik.sh --clean` (removes all data)
